.TH "SVGGraphicsElement.copy_event" "JS" "November 26, 2023" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
SVGGraphicsElement.copy_event \- SVGGraphicsElement: copy event
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]copy\f[B]\f[R] event fires on
\f[CR]SVGGraphicsElements\f[R] when the user initiates a copy action
through the browser\[cq]s user interface.
.PP
The event\[cq]s default action is to copy the selection (if any) to the
clipboard.
.PP
A handler for this event can \f[I]modify\f[R] the clipboard contents by
calling \f[CR]setData(format, data)\f[R] on the event\[cq]s
\f[CR]ClipboardEvent.clipboardData\f[R] property, and cancelling the
event\[cq]s default action using \f[CR]event.preventDefault()\f[R].
.PP
However, the handler cannot \f[I]read\f[R] the clipboard data.
.PP
It\[cq]s possible to construct and dispatch a synthetic \f[CR]copy\f[R]
event, but this will not affect the system clipboard.
.SH SYNTAX
Use the event name in methods like \f[CR]addEventListener()\f[R], or set
an event handler property.
.IP
.EX
addEventListener(\[dq]copy\[dq], (event) => {});

oncopy = (event) => {};
.EE
.SH EVENT TYPE
A \f[CR]ClipboardEvent\f[R].
Inherits from \f[CR]Event\f[R].
.SH EXAMPLE
.SS HTML
.IP
.EX
<?xml version=\[dq]1.0\[dq] encoding=\[dq]UTF\-8\[dq]?>
<svg
  viewBox=\[dq]0 0 100 30\[dq]
  width=\[dq]600\[dq]
  height=\[dq]320\[dq]
  xmlns=\[dq]http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\[dq]>
  <text x=\[dq]5\[dq] y=\[dq]10\[dq] id=\[dq]text\-to\-copy\[dq]>Copy this text</text>
  <foreignObject x=\[dq]5\[dq] y=\[dq]20\[dq] width=\[dq]90\[dq] height=\[dq]20\[dq]>
    <input xmlns=\[dq]http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\[dq] placeholder=\[dq]Paste it here\[dq] />
  </foreignObject>
</svg>
.EE
.SS CSS
.IP
.EX
input {
  font\-size: 10px;
  width: 100%;
  height: 90%;
  box\-sizing: border\-box;
  border: 1px solid black;
}
.EE
.SS JavaScript
.IP
.EX
document.querySelector(\[dq]text\[dq]).addEventListener(\[dq]copy\[dq], (evt) => {
  evt.clipboardData.setData(
    \[dq]text/plain\[dq],
    document.getSelection().toString().toUpperCase(),
  );
  evt.preventDefault();
});
.EE
